-- Nanya Technology Shares Decline in Taipei Trading on January Sales Drop
-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 2011-02-09T01:28:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-09/nanya-technology-shares-decline-in-taipei-trading-on-january-sales-drop.html
  Nanya Technology Corp . shares fell in
Taipei trading after the company reported a decline in its
January sales.  The stock dropped 2.3 percent to NT$18.85 as of 9:19 a.m.
local time. The maker of memory chips said unconsolidated sales
in January fell 27 percent to NT$3.44 billion.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Adela Lin in Taipei at 
